ZH: 他无故迟到了半个小时。
EN: He arrived half an hour late for no reason.

ZH: 我无故收到了一封怪异的邮件。
EN: I received a strange email for no apparent reason.

ZH: 她无故生气，让我很困惑。
EN: She is angry for no reason, which confuses me.

ZH: 这个问题无故变得更加复杂。
EN: This issue has become unnecessarily complicated.

ZH: 我们之间并无故隔，只是有些误会。
EN: There is no reason for us to be estranged, it's just a misunderstanding.

ZH: 他无故怀疑了我的诚实。
EN: He unreasonably doubted my honesty.

ZH: 这种行为无故引起了很多争议。
EN: This behavior has unnecessarily caused a lot of controversy.

ZH: 我不明白为何他无故失去了信任。
EN: I don't understand why he lost trust for no reason.

ZH: 他无故地被解雇了。
EN: He was unreasonably fired.

ZH: 这家公司无故拒绝了我的申请。
EN: The company unreasonably rejected my application.

ZH: 他无故地毁了我的计划。
EN: He ruined my plans for no reason.

ZH: 这种行为无故浪费了时间和精力。
EN: This behavior unnecessarily wastes time and energy.

ZH: 他为何无故选择离开？
EN: Why did he choose to leave for no reason?

ZH: 我们不应该无故放弃希望。
EN: We should not give up hope without reason.

ZH: 他无故对我示好，让我感到困惑。
EN: He showed me kindness for no reason, which confused me.

ZH: 我们不能无故责怪他人。
EN: We should not blame others without reason.

ZH: 他无故地拒绝了我的帮助。
EN: He unreasonably refused my help.

ZH: 这种行为很无故地损害了我们的友谊。
EN: This behavior unreasonably damages our friendship.

ZH: 她无故地丢失了我的钱包。
EN: She lost my wallet for no reason.

ZH: 无故的疑虑会毁掉一段美好的关系。
EN: Unreasonable doubts can ruin a beautiful relationship.
